==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prepotent
<hw>Pre*po"tent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praepotens</ets>. See <er>Pre-</er>, and
<er>Potent</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Very powerful; superior in force, influence, or
authority; predominant.</def> <rj><au>Plaifere.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Characterized by
prepotency.</def> <rj><au>Darwin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preprovide</ent>⟦br⟧
